There are very few works that treat exclusively of petroleum. An article in the
                    Bull, de la Soe. Géol. de France, xxv., gives the best
                    résumé of the mention made by classical writers. Travellers overland to India
                    and Persia have usually described Baku (see Kaempfer, 1712; Hanway, 1743;
                    Foster, 1784; Kinnier, 1848). On the occurrence of petroleum in Burmah, see Journaleof theEmbassies to the Court of Ava, Symes (1795), Crawfurd (1826), Yule (1855);
